# WHAT IT IS
#   `@dcmjs/commands` is the **official command-line interface
#   to the dcmjs DICOM library family** — three pure-Node.js
#   binaries that wrap the typed `dcmjs` library APIs into
#   shell-friendly operations:
#
#     1. **`dcmjs` bin** — manipulate DICOM Part-10 files
#        (the `.dcm` binary container format that every
#        imaging modality writes to disk):
#          dcmjs dump <part10.dcm>       — dump DICOM tags
#          dcmjs instance <part10.dcm>   — write instance data
#                                          (optionally pretty-
#                                           printed via -p)
#
#     2. **`dicomwebjs` bin** — interact with DICOMweb servers
#        (PS3.18 REST):  query, retrieve, and convert between
#        DICOMweb metadata + bulkdata representations and
#        DICOM Part-10 files:
#          dicomwebjs dump <url>         — dump DICOMweb resource
#          dicomwebjs instance <url>     — write instance data
#          dicomwebjs download <url>     — download a full study
#          dicomwebjs part10 <url>       — convert DICOMweb
#                                          metadata to Part-10
#
#     3. **`dimsejs` bin** — interact with classical DICOM
#        DIMSE (PS3.7 wire-protocol) services (the canonical
#        C-FIND / C-MOVE / C-STORE / C-ECHO / C-GET DIMSE
#        primitives used by every PACS, gateway, and modality
#        worklist server in the world):
#          dimsejs study <ae-name>       — query for studies
#
#   These three binaries form a complete CLI complement to the
#   dcmjs library — useful for shell-pipeline integration into
#   medical-imaging research workflows, CI/CD pipelines that
#   need to inspect DICOM artifacts, regression-testing
#   against PACS servers, and ad-hoc one-off conversions
#   between DICOM Part-10 and DICOMweb representations.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from bin/{dcmjs,dicomwebjs,
#                       dimsejs,cliDownload,cliPart10}.js
#                       commander `.command()` registrations;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetches)
#
#   ════════════════ dcmjs ════════════════
#
#   dcmjs <COMMAND> [ARGS...]
#
#   Commands:
#     dump <PART10>                  Dump a DICOM Part-10 file
#                                    (parse + print every Tag/
#                                    VR/Value tree)
#     instance <PART10> [OPTIONS]    Write the instance data
#         -p, --pretty               Pretty-print
#
#   ════════════════ dicomwebjs ════════════════
#
#   dicomwebjs [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <COMMAND> [ARGS...]
#
#   Global options:
#     -s, --study <UID>              Download a specific Study
#                                    Instance UID
#     --seriesUID <UID>              For a specific Series
#                                    Instance UID
#
#   Commands:
#     dump <DICOMWEB_URL>            Dump a DICOMweb resource
#         --debug                    Set debug-level logging
#     instance <PART10> [OPTIONS]    Write the instance data
#         -p, --pretty               Pretty-print
#         --debug                    Set debug-level logging
#     download <URL> [OPTIONS]       Download a full DICOM
#                                    study from any supported
#                                    source
#         -S, --StudyInstanceUID <UID>
#                                    StudyInstanceUID to
#                                    download
#         -d, --directory <DIR>      Download to local directory
#                                    [default: .]
#         --debug                    Enable debug logging
#     part10 <URL> [OPTIONS]         Convert local or remote
#                                    DICOMweb metadata files
#                                    to Part-10
#         -S, --StudyInstanceUID <UID>
#                                    StudyInstanceUID to convert
#         -d, --directory <DIR>      Output directory
#                                    [default: .]
#         --debug                    Enable debug logging
#
#   ════════════════ dimsejs ════════════════
#
#   dimsejs <COMMAND> [ARGS...]
#
#   Commands:
#     study <AE_NAME>                Query for studies at the
#                                    named DICOM AE (Application
#                                    Entity)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `dcmjs-org/dcmjs-commands` declares a **direct** dependency
#   on `dcmjs@^0.41.0` in its `package.json` (verified via `gh
#   api repos/dcmjs-org/dcmjs-commands/contents/package.json`).
#   The bin source files import the typed `dcmjs` library
#   primitives via `import { readDicom, instanceDicom,
#   dumpDicom } from '../src/index.js';` and the library
#   internally re-exports the canonical `dcmjs` APIs.
#
#   `dcmjs-org/dcmjs` is **THE canonical TypeScript / JavaScript
#   DICOM library** — Erik Ziegler, Bill Wallace, Steve Pieper,
#   and the Open Health Imaging Foundation (OHIF) team's
#   reference pure-Node.js implementation of the DICOM Part-5
#   data structure + Part-10 file format + Part-18 JSON
#   encoding.  800+ ★ on GitHub and 200,000+ weekly npm
#   downloads, the de-facto TS/JS DICOM dependency on npm —
#   the only feature-complete browser + Node compatible DICOM
#   library (the alternative `dicomParser` is parse-only and
#   significantly less complete).  dcmjs exposes:
#
#     • Typed `dcmjs.data.DicomMessage.readFile(buffer)` /
#       `DicomMessage.writeFile(dataset)` typed file I/O
#     • Typed `dcmjs.data.DicomDict` with `dict.dict` (the
#       parsed dataset as `{tag: {vr, Value}}`) and
#       `dict.upsertTag(tag, vr, values)` typed mutator API
#     • Typed `dcmjs.data.DicomMetaDictionary.nameMap`,
#       `DicomMetaDictionary.naturalizeDataset(dataset)`,
#       `DicomMetaDictionary.denaturalizeDataset(dataset)`,
#       `DicomMetaDictionary.uid()`, `DicomMetaDictionary.
#       date()`, `DicomMetaDictionary.time()` typed
#       dictionary helpers
#     • Typed `dcmjs.derivations.*` for the canonical DICOM
#       Information Object Definitions (IODs) — typed
#       `derivations.Segmentation` (DICOM segmentation
#       objects, used by every TotalSegmentator / nnU-Net /
#       MONAI inference pipeline), `derivations.StructuredReport`
#       (DICOM SR — radiology reports), `derivations.ParametricMap`
#       (parametric image overlays — perfusion CT, ASL MRI),
#       `derivations.MeasurementReport` (TID 1500
#       measurement-template structured reports),
#       `derivations.Multiframe` (multi-frame image objects —
#       cardiac cine, 4D CT, dynamic-contrast MRI),
#       `derivations.ImageObjectDefinition`
#     • Typed `dcmjs.adapters.Cornerstone.*` /
#       `adapters.OHIF.*` /  `adapters.NIfTI.*` /
#       `adapters.VTKjs.*` typed adapter layers connecting
#       dcmjs to the broader medical-imaging ecosystem
#     • Typed `dcmjs.normalizers.*` for every IOD-specific
#       normalization rule (Segmentation, Structured Report,
#       Spatial Registration, Spatial Fiducials, Radiation
#       Therapy Structure Set, RT Plan, RT Dose, RT Beams)
#     • Typed pixel-data codecs — JPEG Baseline, JPEG
#       Extended, JPEG Lossless, JPEG 2000, JPEG-LS, RLE
#       Lossless (via the sister `dcmjs-codecs` package)
#     • Typed network bindings — `dcmjs.networking.*` provides
#       a typed wrapper around the typed DIMSE PDU protocol
#       that the `dcmjs-dimse` sister package exposes for
#       Node-side C-FIND / C-MOVE / C-STORE / C-ECHO / C-GET
#       operations
#
